Mar 23 2008 	Satisfied with Europa House	My wife and I and our two teenaged daughters stayed at Europa House for 5 nights in mid-March in one of their quad rooms. Unlike in North America, European hotels don't tend to consider that families of four people often like to share the same room when they travel as booking two separate rooms becomes very expensive. As such I was pleased to find that EH Hotel had rooms for up to 5 people at very reasonable rates considering their central location just a block from Paddington station. Some of the previous Trip Advisor reviews of this place had given us pause, however. Fortunately the room (after some initial booking issues over the internet) turned out to be clean (enough) and very adequate. The bathroom wasn't a highlight as it was very tiny and the toilet seemed to consider the flush lever as more of a suggestion than an order. Still the shower had great pressure and hot water and the bathroom seemed clean. The breakfast was included and did fill you up but wasn't changed at all from day to day so by Day 5 we were tired of it. The front desk staff was helpful and even kept our luggage in a locked room for us on checkout day so we could sightsee for the day without it when we only left town in the evening. I definitely recommend this hotel for budget-minded travellers/families who want a basic clean room in central London.	
